The term "confluence home" is confusing. Standard practice (like java_home) is to refer to the install dir as home directory. We could continue to call it confluence-home internally in our code, but it should be changed publicly. It's a big change in docs, but it could be done with the global search & replace plugin.

"Confluence-data" seems like a good replacement.

